pageContext.claim: “I was for Strange, and I brought Strange up 20 points. Just so you understand. When I endorsed him, he was in fifth place. He went way up. Almost 20 points.”
pageContext.analysis: Polls indicate that Trump's endorsement made little difference -- and in fact Strange lost to Ray Moore by a greater margin than polls suggested at the time of Trump's endorsement. And while Trump says Strange was in fifth place, there were only three candidates in the primary. Indeed, when Trump endorsed Strange in early August, two of the last three polls showed him in a virtual tie for first place.
